latestIgtvVideos.title: How to treat Comedones overnight / Control Acne ✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey ! 

I found these helpful in controlling Acne + treating your comedones or tiny little bumps. Tried and tested and found it extremely helpful! I also have another combination which helps. Will share that soon :)

Products used :
1) @righteousessentials Hemp & Camelia cleansing oil. Started using it since 3 days and I love how soothing it is ! It’s a non emulsifying oil. Doesn’t feel heavy and removes makeup / sunscreen effectively. You can use any cleansing oil for this but I loved this ❤️

2) @eclat_official.in Acne edit Facewash - This is a lovely facewash for oily / acne prone skin types. Very gentle yet effective. It’s an exfoliating cleanser , do not use more than 3 times a week. It cleanses and soothe my skin. Love it ! If you have tiny bumps , try using this and see the change for yourself ! 

3) @eclat_official.in Acne edit Mask - it’s such a must have mask for oily / acne - prone skin types. It detox’s your skin perfectly by cleaning out extra sebum , dirt / impurities.  I love to use it on my T-Zone / on my acne. Dries out real quick and so effective. You can literally see the gunk coming off ! 

4) @klairs.in Supple preparation toner - after detoxing , I love using a hydrating toner and what’s better than this ?

5) @theearthrhythm HA - Have you seen any of my routines without a HA these days ? You know my views about this already. 

6) @pure_bubbles_skincare Clarity lotion - being honest at first I didn’t understand the hype about this one. I felt this isn’t suiting my skin at all. Never judge a product initially! When my skin felt congested and knew it’s prone to acne , I tried this consistently ! It does what it says. I can see it controls tiny bumps over night. YES YES YES !  It’s light weight and perfect for summers ! My skin is getting used to this beauty and I love that !
